<plot>This film was ten years in the making but S. Pearl Sharp was determined that it be made. This powerful documentary explores the residual impact of the African Halocaust, slavery and its reverberations in the world today. It takes a colorful look at genetic memory, psychological trauma and community consciousness in present day behavior.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?563836</url></doc>
